        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out: <m>\frac{5}{9} \times \frac{2}{3}</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    To multiply two fractions, multiply numerators and denominators separately and simplify the resulting fraction to its simplest form.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\frac{5}{9} \times \frac{2}{3} \amp = \frac{5 \times 2}{9 \times 3}</mrow>
                        <mrow></mrow>
                        <mrow> \amp = \frac{10}{27} </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
